originalText.text: As per recommendation of  my 80-year mother's primary physician, I made an appointment for her to see Dr. Dominguez. I looked him up on Google and he was listed that he is associated with Presbyterian Hospital, which is what I was looking for  He is not! He is associated with Lenox Hill.  It is a poorly run storefront!  Stay away!  The fire alarm continues to alert it needs new batteries, the front desk receptionist does not seem happy to be there, even though there are signs of no cell phone use patients are bellowing their cell phone conversations, and it all seems quite disorganized. Patients wait and wait some more. We waited an hour and the doctor had not arrived.  We were about to leave when the assistant called my Mom's name. She informed us that Dr. Dominguez's partner would attend my Mom that he was not coming into the office (of course, we were not informed when arrived at the front desk).  We left!  I was applaud at the doctors' disrespect for the community --an already disenfranchised people.
